## 🛠️ Implemented Components

### 1. Root Configurations & Layout
- **[package.json](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/package.json)**: Configured with Next.js 16.2.6, React 19.2.4, Tailwind CSS v4, named `vedicdharma-engine@0.1.0`.
- **[tsconfig.json](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/tsconfig.json)**: Configured TypeScript compilation targets and path mapping.
- **[layout.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/app/layout.tsx)**: Added Google Fonts mapping for optimal typography:
  - `Inter` (sans-serif) for system utilities and control elements.
  - `Crimson Pro` (serif) for the English translations and literary text.
  - `Noto Sans Devanagari` (Sanskrit) to ensure perfect rendering of Vedic svaras (accents).
  - Configured `suppressHydrationWarning` on `html` and `body` elements to suppress extension class injection warnings.
- **[globals.css](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/app/globals.css)**: Implemented styling variables for warm light paper and dark stone themes, premium custom scrollbars, and golden accent highlight glows.

### 2. Main Landing Page (`/`)
- **[page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/app/page.tsx)**: Converted into an interactive client component containing:
  - **Refined Hero Hierarchy**: Swapped image caption text with a tight, direct value proposition.
  - **Sanskrit Shloka Highlight**: Centered Mantra 1.1.1, increasing the font size and wrapping it in a golden-bordered blockquote.
  - **Live Demo Sandbox**: Created an interactive sandbox section. Users can click individual words in Mantra 1.1.1 to see the un-sandhied Padapatha form, root lemma, grammatical traits, and literal meanings appear in real-time.
  - **Scannable Paradigm Comparison**: Restructured the text detailing the *Layered Disclosure Model* into a side-by-side card grid highlighting *The Traditional Overhead* vs *The DLIIH Solution*.
  - **TEI/XML Syntax Display**: Added a dedicated technical section demonstrating academic rigor. Features a tabbed code block toggling between raw **TEI/XML Source** and formatted **JSON Payload**.
  - **Expanded Global Navigation**: Refined the sticky header with clean links: *Home*, *Corpus Viewer*, *Interactive Sandbox*, *TEI/XML Schema*, *Roadmap*, and *GitHub*.

### 3. Veda Selection Wizard Portal (`/texts`)
- **[page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/app/texts/page.tsx)**:
  - Guided step-by-step wizard to dynamically browse all 4 Vedas.
  - **Step 1**: Choose from the 4 Vedas (Rigveda, Yajurveda, Samaveda, Atharvaveda) with custom card layouts, descriptions, and translations of their names.
  - **Step 2**: Choose from historical Shakhas (recensions) specific to that Veda.
  - **Step 3**: Select the Mandala (Rigveda) or Kanda (Yajurveda/Atharvaveda) or Prapathaka (Samaveda).
  - **Step 4**: Select the Sukta or Hymn.
  - **Action**: Routes to the dynamic reader via the primary "Begin Exploration" button.

### 4. Dynamic Veda Reader (`/texts/[veda]/[shakha]/[mandala]/[sukta]`)
- **[page.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/app/texts/[veda]/[shakha]/[mandala]/[sukta]/page.tsx)**:
  - Automatically parses route parameters `veda`, `shakha`, `mandala`, and `sukta`.
  - **Active Dataset (Rigveda Sakala 1.1)**: Dynamically loads and parses the Rigveda dataset from [rv_1_1.json](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/data/rv_1_1.json). Features click-to-inspect word alignments, morphological breakdown sidebar, and Sāyaṇa's Sanskrit commentaries.
  - **Roadmap Placeholder (Other Vedas/Shakhas)**: If users select sections that are not yet digitized, it renders a beautifully formatted placeholder detailing the DLIIH roadmap, with a quick-link button to jump back to the active Rigveda 1.1 dataset.
  - **Mobile Drawer**: The split pane collapses into an overlay bottom sheet on mobile viewports.

### 5. DLIIH Scholar AI Chatbot
- **[Chatbot.tsx](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/app/components/Chatbot.tsx)**: A floating interactive widget with auto-scroll and loading indicators, styled with the dark-stone theme.
- **[route.ts](file:///c:/Users/sachi/Downloads/rigveda-mvp/app/api/chat/route.ts)**: A server-side API handler that returns rich context-aware explanations on terms like *Agni*, *Rishi*, *Gayatri*, *Sayana*, *Rta*, *Purohita*, and *Hotr*.

